text: Uíge (briefly Carmona) is a town in northwestern Angola. It is the capital of Uíge Province. There are 119,815.http://bevoelkerungsstatistik.de/wg.php?x=&men;=gcis&lng;=de&des;=wg&srt;=npan&col;=abcdefghinoq&msz;=1500&geo;=-19 people. When Portuguese were there in the 1950s, it was a major center for coffee production. ==References== Category:Cities in Angola
title: Uíge
